Metadata-Version: 1.1
Name: zerotest
Version: 1.2.0
Summary: Lazy guy's testing tool. Capture HTTP traffic and generate python integration test for your API server.
Home-page: https://github.com/jjyr/zerotest
Author: Hari Jiang
Author-email: hari.jiang@outlook.com
License: MIT
Description: ZEROTEST |PyPI| |Travis|
        ========================
        
        Zerotest makes it easy to test API server, start a micro proxy, send
        requests, and generate test code by these behaviours.
        
            *Zerotest makes test api server like a boss!*
        
        Install
        -------
        
        Stable version: ``pip install zerotest``
        
        Develop version:
        ``pip install git+https://github.com/jjyr/zerotest.git``
        
        **zerotest require python2.7 or 3.2+**
        
        Usage
        -----
        
        1. Start a local proxy to capture http traffic
           ``zerotest server https://api.github.com -f octocat.data``
        
        2. Make few requests ``curl -i http://localhost:7000/users/octocat``
        
        3. Press ``C-c`` to exit local proxy
        
        4. Generate test code
           ``zerotest generate octocat.data --ignore-all-headers > test_octocat.py``
        
        5. Type ``py.test test_octocat.py`` to run test
        
        Develop
        -------
        
        Export debug flag ``ZEROTEST_DEBUG=true`` to see verbose logs during
        program or test running.
        
        Contributors
        ------------
        
        `Contributors <https://github.com/jjyr/zerotest/graphs/contributors>`__
        
        Contribute
        ----------
        
        -  Open issue if found bugs or some cool ideas
        -  Feel free to ask if have any questions
        -  Testing is very important for a test tool, commit your test file
           together with pull request
        
